objects.name: NCSC
objects.description: The National Cyber Security Centre (NCSC) is the primary author and publisher of this malware analysis report, providing threat intelligence, technical analysis, and detection rules.

objects.name: Keylogger dropper executable
objects.description: Malicious dropper that installs the keylogger DLL. Associated with Wishful Woodchuck campaigns.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'msvrt.exe' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'unknown (location from which executed)']

objects.name: Keylogger DLL (x86)
objects.description: Malicious DLL containing keylogging functionality, dropped by msvrt.exe. Uses exported functions for keystroke capture.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'lMM32.dll' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'unknown (location from which executed)']

objects.name: Keylogger DLL (x86)
objects.description: Malicious keylogger DLL for x86, participates in keystroke logging for Wishful Woodchuck.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'hlpapi.dll' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'unknown (location from which executed)']

objects.name: Keylogger DLL (x64)
objects.description: Malicious executable responsible for injecting the keylogger DLL for x64 Windows systems.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'Manualmap_injector.exe' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'unknown (location from which executed)']

objects.name: Keylogger log file
objects.description: XOR-obfuscated logfile written by Wishful Woodchuck keylogger to record captured keystrokes.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'msimm.dat' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'unknown (location from which executed)']

objects.name: Keylogger DLL (x64)
objects.description: Malicious keylogger DLL for x64, identified in retro-hunt analysis as a Wishful Woodchuck variant.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'lMM64.dll' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'unknown (location from which executed)']

objects.name: Keylogger DLL (x64, VMProtect packed)
objects.description: Malicious, VMProtect-packed version of the x64 keylogger DLL. Linked to Wishful Woodchuck retro-hunts.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'Manualmap_injector.vmp.exe' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'unknown (location from which executed)']

objects.name: Keylogger executable (x86)
objects.description: Malicious executable file for x86, variant of Wishful Woodchuck. Identified through retro-hunt; multiple sizes exist.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'WEXTRACT.EXE' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'unknown (location from which executed)']

objects.name: Masquerading file description
objects.description: Malicious file description used by lMM32.dll to masquerade as legitimate Windows IMM32 binary.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'lMM32.dll (malicious DLL)' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'unknown (location from which executed)']

objects.name: wishful woodchuck
objects.description: Wishful Woodchuck is a non-persistent Windows keylogger that hooks the keyboard using Windows API calls and logs keystrokes to a file on disk. It features XOR-encoded logging with a static, multi-byte key embedded in the binary, and employs several defense evasion techniques, including string obfuscation and masquerading as legitimate Windows files. The malware contains no persistence or communications functionality, and relies on running in memory until the host is rebooted. Variants have been observed as both executables and DLLs for x86 and x64 architectures. Observed techniques and versioning strongly suggest a link to the Turla threat actor group.

objects.name: Turla
objects.description: Turla is a threat actor group suspected of developing or operating the Wishful Woodchuck keylogger. The malware utilizes XOR 0x55 obfuscation and a TVer versioning string, both previously associated with Turla-operated malware. Turla is known for advanced persistence and defense evasion TTPs and has been linked to various espionage campaigns targeting governmental and diplomatic entities.

objects.name: MITRE ATT&CK
objects.description: MITRE ATT&CK framework is referenced as a globally accessible knowledge base for cataloguing adversary tactics and techniques observed in relation to Wishful Woodchuck.

objects.name: wishfulwoodchuck_hardcoded_xorkey
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern:
rule wishfulwoodchuck_hardcoded_xorkey
{
    meta:
        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Finds binaries containing the hardcoded XOR key
from the keylogger binaries"

    strings:
        $xorkey = {0A 19 59 2D 6C 59 6F FA 8B 6F 9B FF 37 9B BD 7B 59 4B
7B DD 0F 64 91 C7 D6 9C 6F 7B 9C 01 9C 91 79 C7 C8 C9 DF E1 FA FF 04 08
59 E6 64 6D 37 9B 38 81 2D 81 65 7D 66 9A}

    condition:

uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and
uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and
all of them

}

objects.name: wishfulwoodchuck_file_description
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern:
rule wishfulwoodchuck_file_description
{
    meta:
        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Unique file description"

strings:

$description = "Multi-User Windows IMM32 API CIient DLL" wide

condition:

uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and
uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and
all of them

}

objects.name: wishfulwoodchuck_logfile_encodedheader
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern:
rule wishfulwoodchuck_logfile_encodedheader
{
    meta:
        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Encoded log file header"

    strings:
        $header = {41 19 0A 2D 20 59 5F FA 81 6F CF FF 61 9B D8 7B 2B 4B
46}
    condition:
        all of them
}
